  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.64,
      "end": 5.46,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.44,
      "end": 10.68,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 11.82,
      "end": 14.24,
      "text": "Esaups Fables, the old lion.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 15.78,
      "end": 23.02,
      "text": "A lion, infabled by age and no longer able to procure food for himself by force, determined to do so by cunning.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 23.68,
      "end": 28.22,
      "text": "Be taking himself to a cave, he lay down inside and feigned to be sick.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 29.1,
      "end": 34.62,
      "text": "And whenever any of the other animals entered to inquire after his health, he sprang upon them and devoured them.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 35.5,
      "end": 41.8,
      "text": "Many lost their lives in this way. To one day a fox called it the cave, and having a suspicion of the truth,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 42.24,
      "end": 46.42,
      "text": "addressed the lion from outside instead of going in, and asked him how he did.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 47.22,
      "end": 49.58,
      "text": "He replied that he was in a very bad way.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 50.16,
      "end": 54.46,
      "text": "But said he, why do you stand outside? Pray come in.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 55.56,
      "end": 63.08,
      "text": "I should have done so, answered the fox, if I hadn't noticed that all the footprints point towards the cave and none the other way.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 64.62,
      "end": 66.38,
      "text": "End of the old lion.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
